ersonal Profile</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">People Story</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Lindsay Barnett</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Playground Productions</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/07/16/multimedia/13ST-BACKYARD-BASEBALL-portraits-01-lcvj/13ST-BACKYARD-BASEBALL-portraits-01-lcvj-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Akilah Townsend for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>“I had blind confidence,” Lindsay Barnett said, describing her mind-set at the start of her quest.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Data Centers to Add Billions in Power Costs in 13 States</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/14/business/energy-environment/pjm-electricity-prices-data-centers.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/14/business/energy-environment/pjm-electricity-prices-data-centers.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/14/business/energy-environment/pjm-electricity-prices-data-centers.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>A power auction conducted by a giant grid operator is expected to add $6.3 billion in additional charges to consumers and businesses because of electricity needs of data centers.</description><dc:creator>Ivan Penn</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2026 00:25:48 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Data center</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Electric power</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Price</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US states</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">PJM Interconnection</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Regulation and Deregulation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Federal Energy Regulatory Commission</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Governors</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Josh Shapiro</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Pennsylvania</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_geo">Mid-Atlantic States (US)</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Federalism</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/07/14/multimedia/14biz-pjm-rates-sub-vjgq/14biz-pjm-rates-sub-vjgq-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Leah Millis/Reuters</media:credit><media:description>Northern Virginia is home to several data centers, including the Digital Realty Data Center in Ashburn.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Twitter Turns 20: Two Decades of Memes, Movements and Hot Takes</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/15/technology/twitter-x-20-years.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/15/technology/twitter-x-20-years.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/15/technology/twitter-x-20-years.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The first tweets from the public appeared on July 15, 2006, several months after a soft launch. It was rebranded as X after being acquired by Elon Musk.</description><dc:creator>Neil Vigdor</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2026 09:00:08 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">X</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Social Media</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Elon Musk</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Black People</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">African American</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">African-American</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Michael J Massimino</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Space</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Donald Trump</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US Politics</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">MeToo Movement</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Chadwick Boseman</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/07/15/multimedia/15xp-twitter-bzwh/15xp-twitter-bzwh-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Thor Swift for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>On July 15, 2006, a new era of provocative hot takes, kneejerk reactions and random thoughts on social media ushered itself in with the public debut of Twitter, after a soft launch that March.</media:description></media:content></item></channel></rss>